==English==

===Etymology===
A later {{etyl|enm|en}} spelling, retaining the breathy {{term|-s}}, of {{term|hennes|lang=enm}}, ({{term|henne|lang=enm}} + adverbial genitive ending {{term|-s|lang=enm}}), from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|heonan||lang=ang|away", "hence}}, from a West Germanic root *hin- (compare Old Saxon [[hinan]], Old High German [[hinnan]], German [[hinnen]], Dutch [[heen]], Swedish [[hän]]); related to Old English {{term|her||lang=ang|here}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈhɛns/}}
